#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/altinstall.xml:164
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installation from non-Gentoo LiveCDs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/altinstall.xml:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/altinstall.xml:170
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The Gentoo developers cannot support you if something goes wrong with a\n"
"non-Gentoo LiveCD, as there's no way to fix, troubleshoot, or document every\n"
"quirk of every LiveCD out there. Only Gentoo LiveCDs are officially supported.\n"
"If you run into problems with alternative installation media, please visit the\n"
"<uri link=\"http://forums.gentoo.org\">Gentoo Forums</uri> for community help.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/altinstall.xml:178
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It is possible to boot some other LiveCD besides the Gentoo-provided CDs. This\n"
"will give you a functional environment to use while you're compiling and\n"
"installing Gentoo. The instructions provided here should work in principle with\n"
"just about any other LiveCD.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/altinstall.xml:185
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There are too many LiveCDs out there to <uri\n"
"link=\"http://distrowatch.com/search.php\">list</uri>, but you might try <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.knoppix.org/\">Knoppix</uri>. It provides a full graphical\n"
"desktop, with office applications, web browsers, and games to keep you busy.\n"
"Knoppix is only available for x86 users, so depending on your needs you may need\n"
"to find a different LiveCD.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><warn>
#: en/altinstall.xml:194
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Be aware that if you save anything in your LiveCD's home directory while waiting\n"
"for your Gentoo system to install, it will not be available when you reboot\n"
"into Gentoo. Be sure to save important files on the hard disk or on some other\n"
"computer!\n"
msgstr ""
"Gentooシステムがインストールされるのを待つ間にKnoppixのホームディレクトリに何かを保存した場合、\n"
"再起動後にGentooからそれを利用することはできません。重要なデータはハードディスクや何か他のコンピュータに保存するのを忘れないでください！\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/altinstall.xml:203
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Installation instructions"
msgstr "nfs-utilsのインストール"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/altinstall.xml:207
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Boot from your LiveCD. Open a terminal and run <c>su -</c> so you can change your\n"
"password. This lets you set the root password for the CD. You can now configure\n"
"<c>sshd</c> for remote login, if you need to install Gentoo remotely. Next,\n"
"you'll need to create the <path>/mnt/gentoo</path> mountpoint.\n"
msgstr ""
"通常、KnoppixではKDEのデスクトップが起動します。パスワードを変更できるようにするために、\n"
"<c>konsole</c>を起動し<c>su -</c>を実行してください。これによってKnoppixでのroot ユーザのパスワードを設定できます。\n"
"ここで、リモートログインのために<c>sshd</c>を必要に応じて設定できます。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/altinstall.xml:213
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Creating the /mnt/gentoo mountpoint"
msgstr "マウントポイント /mnt/gentoo の作成"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/altinstall.xml:214
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>mkdir /mnt/gentoo</i>\n"
msgstr "# <i>mkdir /mnt/gentoo</i>\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/altinstall.xml:218
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"At this point, you can pick up with the standard install documentation at <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=1&amp;chap=4\">part 4</uri>.\n"
"However, when you are asked to mount the proc system, issue the following\n"
"command instead:\n"
msgstr ""
"この時点で、標準的なインストールの手引きの\n"
"<uri link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=1&amp;chap=4\">パート4</uri>\n"
"(訳注: <uri link=\"/doc/ja/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=1&amp;chap=4\">日本語版パート4</uri>)の部分から続けてください。\n"
"ただし、procシステムをマウントするときには、替わりに次のコマンドを実行してください。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/altinstall.xml:224
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Bind-mounting the proc pseudo filesystem"
msgstr "proc仮想ファイルシステムのバインドマウント"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/altinstall.xml:225
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>mount -o bind /proc /mnt/gentoo/proc</i>\n"
msgstr "# <i>mount -o bind /proc /mnt/gentoo/proc</i>\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/altinstall.xml:229
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When you're ready to unpack the stage tarball in <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=1&amp;chap=5#doc_chap2_sect2\">part\n"
"5</uri>, you will need to use a different <c>tar</c> command to ensure that\n"
"proper group IDs are enforced on the unpacked stage:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/altinstall.xml:235
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Unpacking the stage tarball"
msgstr "stage tarballを展開"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/altinstall.xml:236
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>tar --numeric-owner -xvjpf stage3-*.tar.bz2</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/altinstall.xml:240
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once you're ready to chroot into your unpacked stage in <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=1&amp;chap=6#doc_chap1\">part\n"
"6</uri>, you will need to use a different chroot command sequence. This ensures\n"
"that your environment variables are properly setup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/altinstall.xml:246
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Chrooting into the new environment"
msgstr "新しいクライアントの起動"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/altinstall.xml:247
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Some LiveCDs use a funny environment setup, hence the -i option for\n"
"cleaning it up to a reasonable state.)</comment>\n"
"# <i>chroot /mnt/gentoo /bin/env -i TERM=$TERM /bin/bash</i>\n"
"# <i>env-update</i>\n"
"# <i>source /etc/profile</i>\n"
"# <i>export PS1=\"(chroot) $PS1\"</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/altinstall.xml:256
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Finally, know that some Portage FEATURES may not work in your LiveCD. Especially\n"
"watch out for <c>userpriv</c> and <c>usersandbox</c>. If you find yourself\n"
"getting errors, it might be wise to disable some or all of the optional\n"
"FEATURES.\n"
msgstr ""
"また、KNOPPIXでは、PortageのFEATURES内のいくつかが動作しないことも知られています。\n"
"とりわけ、<c>userpriv</c>と<c>usersandbox</c>に注意してください。\n"
"もし、エラーが発生したら、オプション機能のいくつか、または全部を無効にすることが賢明でしょう。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/altinstall.xml:290
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Diskless install using PXE boot"
msgstr "ディスクを使わず、PXEブートを利用したインストール方法"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/altinstall.xml:292 en/altinstall.xml:553
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Requirements"
msgstr "必要なもの"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/altinstall.xml:296
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You will need a network card on the diskless client that uses the PXE protocol\n"
"to boot, like many 3com cards. You will also need a BIOS that supports booting\n"
"from PXE.\n"
msgstr ""
"ディスクを持たないクライアントには、多くの3comのカードのような、ブートの際にPXEプロトコルを使えるネットワークカードが必要です。\n"
"また、PXEによるブートをサポートしたBIOSも必要です。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/altinstall.xml:304
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Server base setup"
msgstr "サーバ上のベースセットアップ"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/altinstall.xml:308
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Create directories: The first thing to do is to create the directories where\n"
"your diskless system will be stored. Create a directory called\n"
"<path>/diskless</path> which houses a directory for each diskless client. For\n"
"the rest of this howto we'll be working on the client 'eta'.\n"
msgstr ""
"ディレクトリの作成: まず最初に、ディスクレスのシステムが保存されるディレクトリを作成します。\n"
"それぞれのディスクレスのクライアントをホストするために、<path>/diskless</path>のようなディレクトリを作成してください。\n"
"これ以降、この手引きでは'eta'という名前のクライアントのセットアップ作業をすることにします。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/altinstall.xml:314
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Directory setup"
msgstr "ディレクトリの作成"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/altinstall.xml:315
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>mkdir /diskless</i>\n"
"# <i>mkdir /diskless/eta</i>\n"
"# <i>mkdir /diskless/eta/boot</i>\n"
msgstr ""
"# <i>mkdir /diskless</i>\n"
"# <i>mkdir /diskless/eta</i>\n"
"# <i>mkdir /diskless/eta/boot</i>\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/altinstall.xml:321
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"DHCP and TFTP setup: The client will get boot informations using DHCP and\n"
"download all the required files using TFTP.\n"
msgstr ""
"DHCPとTFTPの設定: クライアントはDHCPを使ってブート情報を取得し、\n"
"TFTP を使って必要なファイルすべてをダウンロードします。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/altinstall.xml:326
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For dhcpd, just run <c>emerge dhcp</c> (or any other DHCP server of your\n"
"choice). Make sure that the correct interface is selected in\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/dhcpd</path>, and configure it for your basic needs. Then, add\n"
"the following on <path>/etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf</path>.\n"
msgstr ""
"dhcpdについては、<c>emerge dhcp</c>（もしくは、選んだ他のDHCPサーバー）を実行してください。\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/dhcpd</path>のなかで正しいインタフェースが選択されていることを確認して、\n"
"基本設定をしてください。その後、次の内容を<path>/etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf</path>に加えてください。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/altinstall.xml:333
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This provides a static IP address for the client and the path of a PXE boot\n"
"image, here <path>pxegrub</path>. You have to replace the MAC address of the\n"
"ethernet card of the client and the directory where you will put the client\n"
"files with the one you use.\n"
msgstr ""
"下の例では静的なIPアドレスと、\n"
"ここでは<path>pxegrub</path>と名付けたPXE用のブートイメージまでのパスをクライアントに対して割り当てています。\n"
"クライアントのイーサ−ネットカードのMACアドレスと、\n"
"それぞれのファイルを保存する場所は状況にあわせて書き換えてください。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/altinstall.xml:339
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "dhcpd.conf"
msgstr "dhcpd.conf"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/altinstall.xml:340
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"option option-150 code 150 = text ;\n"
"ddns-update-style none ;\n"
"host eta {\n"
"hardware ethernet 00:00:00:00:00:00;\n"
"fixed-address <i>ip.add.re.ss</i>;\n"
"option option-150 \"/eta/boot/grub.lst\";\n"
"filename \"/eta/boot/pxegrub\";\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"option option-150 code 150 = text ;\n"
"ddns-update-style none ;\n"
"host eta {\n"
"hardware ethernet 00:00:00:00:00:00;\n"
"fixed-address <i>ip.add.re.ss</i>;\n"
"option option-150 \"/eta/boot/grub.lst\";\n"
"filename \"/eta/boot/pxegrub\";\n"
"}\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/altinstall.xml:351
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next you'll need to configure your interface in <path>/etc/conf.d/net</path> so\n"
"that it doesn't get cleared at bootup. See\n"
"<path>/usr/share/doc/openrc-*/net.example.bz2</path> for more information.\n"
msgstr ""
"次にブートアップ時にクリアされないように、<path>/etc/conf.d/net</path>でインタフェースを設定する必要があります。\n"
"詳しくは<path>/etc/conf.d/net.example</path>をみてください。\n"

